{
  "$schema": "https://aka.ms/codetour-schema",
  "title": "🧪 Scroll Test (Long Steps)",
  "description": "A deliberately verbose tour for reproducing and verifying the comment-widget scroll-cutoff fix. Every step has a long description that should overflow the default box height.",
  "steps": [
    {
      "file": "src/player/index.ts",
      "line": 231,
      "description": "### 🧪 Step 1 — Initial render & the scroll bug\n\nThis step is intentionally **very long** so the CodeTour box overflows its default height. The point is to confirm that you can scroll all the way to the bottom of this content *immediately* when the box opens — **without** having to nudge or resize it first.\n\n#### What to look for\n\n1. The box opens on this step.\n2. You should be able to scroll from the very top of this text down to the **END MARKER** at the bottom right away.\n3. If you can only scroll part way before it stops, and resizing unlocks the rest, the bug is still present.\n\n#### Background\n\nThe tour content is rendered with VS Code's Comments API as an inline `CommentThread` widget. The widget measures its scrollable body height during the initial render, before the Markdown finishes laying out. That left long content clipped until a manual resize forced a relayout.\n\n#### The fix\n\nAfter a step renders, `relayoutThread()` re-assigns the thread's comments on a short delay, which forces VS Code to re-measure the body height and unlock scrolling automatically.\n\n```ts\nfunction relayoutThread(thread: CommentThread) {\n  setTimeout(() => {\n    if (store.activeTour?.thread !== thread) return;\n    try {\n      thread.comments = [...thread.comments];\n    } catch {\n      // disposed\n    }\n  }, 100);\n}\n```\n\n#### Filler so this overflows for sure\n\n- Line of content number one, with enough words to wrap onto a second visual line in a typical editor width.\n- Line of content number two, again padded out so the widget has to grow taller than its default.\n- Line of content number three, more words, more wrapping, more height consumed.\n- Line of content number four, keep going, we want this comfortably past the cutoff point.\n- Line of content number five, almost there, just a bit more vertical space needed.\n- Line of content number six, this should do it on most screens.\n- Line of content number seven, extra insurance for large monitors.\n- Line of content number eight, still going for very large monitors.\n\n> If you can read this blockquote and the marker below the moment the box opens, the fix works. 🎉\n\n**⛳ END MARKER — Step 1.** If you reached this without resizing, scrolling is fixed."
    },
    {
      "file": "src/recorder/index.ts",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "### 🧪 Step 2 — Navigation between long steps\n\nThis second long step verifies the fix **also** applies when you navigate (Next/Previous), not just on the first open. Each navigation disposes the old thread and renders a new one, so the relayout has to fire every time.\n\n#### Checklist\n\n1. You arrived here via **Next** from Step 1.\n2. This content should be fully scrollable to the bottom marker right away.\n3. Press **Previous** to go back, then **Next** again — it should keep working on every step.\n\n#### More filler to guarantee overflow\n\n1. Numbered item one, padded with extra words so it wraps and adds height to the widget body.\n2. Numbered item two, more words, more height, pushing well past the default cutoff.\n3. Numbered item three, continuing to fill vertical space deliberately.\n4. Numbered item four, still adding lines of content here.\n5. Numbered item five, keep stacking it up.\n6. Numbered item six, getting tall now.\n7. Numbered item seven, taller still.\n8. Numbered item eight, plenty for most layouts.\n9. Numbered item nine, insurance for big screens.\n10. Numbered item ten, that should be more than enough.\n\nSome inline `code`, a [link](command:codetour.nextTourStep), and a final paragraph of prose to round things out. The goal is simply to exceed the box's natural height so the scroll behavior is exercised.\n\n**⛳ END MARKER — Step 2.** Reached this without a resize? Navigation relayout works too."
    },
    {
      "file": "package.json",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "### 🧪 Step 3 — Final long step\n\nLast step. Same idea: long enough to overflow, and the **Finish Tour** control plus this bottom marker should both be reachable immediately.\n\n#### Verify\n\n- Scroll to the bottom right away. ✅\n- The navigation row (Previous / Finish Tour) is reachable. ✅\n\n#### Closing filler\n\nParagraph one: lorem-style filler text padded out with enough words to wrap across multiple visual lines and consume real vertical space inside the comment widget body so that the default height is clearly exceeded on a normal editor.\n\nParagraph two: more of the same, because we want zero ambiguity about whether the content overflows. If it doesn't overflow on your screen, make your editor shorter or zoom in and replay.\n\nParagraph three: and a little extra on top, just to be safe across font sizes and display scaling.\n\n- bullet a\n- bullet b\n- bullet c\n- bullet d\n- bullet e\n\n**⛳ END MARKER — Step 3.** If you got here cleanly on open, the scroll-cutoff fix is verified across first-render and navigation."
    }
  ]
}
